<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="156" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,764,503,751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">
<emphasis box="[151,430,503,527]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">
Notes – 
<taxonomicName box="[237,430,503,527]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Plagiochilaceae" genus="Plagiochila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="156" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="barteri">Plagiochila barteri</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[627,759,503,527]" name="Madagascar" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[113,213,535,559]" name="Comoros" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">Comoros</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[225,331,535,559]" name="Mauritius" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[385,514,535,559]" name="Réunion" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">La Réunion</collectingCountry>
, but the 
<taxonomicName box="[609,717,535,559]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Plagiochilaceae" genus="Plagiochila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="156" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="variety" species="barteri" variety="valida">
var. 
<emphasis box="[652,717,535,559]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">valida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was so far only reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[386,514,567,591]" name="Réunion" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">La Réunion</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="WIGGINTON" box="[531,728,567,591]" firstAuthor="WIGGINTON" pageId="3" pageNumber="156" pagination="9" refId="ref3835" refString="WIGGINTON, M. J. (2018). Checklist and distribution of the liverworts and hornworts of sub-Saharan Africa, including the East African Islands (edition 4, 25 June 2018). Trop. Bryol. Res. Rep. 9." type="journal article" year="2018">WIGGINTON, 2018</bibRefCitation>
). It is easily distinguishable from 
<taxonomicName authority="Mitt. var. barteri" box="[424,687,599,623]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Plagiochilaceae" genus="Plagiochila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="156" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="variety" species="barteri" variety="barteri">
<emphasis box="[424,515,599,623]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">P.barteri</emphasis>
Mitt.var. 
<emphasis box="[619,687,599,623]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">barteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has previously been recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[487,615,631,655]" name="Madagascar" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="MARLINE, L. &amp; R. L. ANDRIAMIARISOA &amp; J. BARDAT &amp; M. CHUAH-PETIOT &amp; T. A. J. HEDDERSON &amp; C. REEB &amp; D. STRASBERG &amp; N. WILDING &amp; C. AH-PENG" journalOrPublisher="Cryptogam. Bryol." pageId="3" pageNumber="156" pagination="199 - 255" part="33" refId="ref3810" refString="MARLINE, L., R. L. ANDRIAMIARISOA, J. BARDAT, M. CHUAH-PETIOT, T. A. J. HEDDERSON, C. REEB, D. STRASBERG, N. WILDING &amp; C. AH-PENG (2012). Checklist of the bryophytes of Madagascar. Cryptogam. Bryol. 33: 199 - 255." title="Checklist of the bryophytes of Madagascar" type="journal article" year="2012">MARLINE et al., 2012</bibRefCitation>
), by the dorsal margin almost free of teeth (or with a few ones, &lt;6), and the bulging trigones between leaf cells (
<bibRefCitation author="VANDEN BERGHEN, C." box="[124,389,727,751]" journalOrPublisher="Bull. Jard. Bot. Belg." pageId="3" pageNumber="156" pagination="41 - 103" part="51" refId="ref4187" refString="VANDEN BERGHEN, C. (1981). Le genre Plagiochila (Dum.) Dum. (Hepaticae) a Madagascar et aux Mascareignes, principalement d'apres les recoltes de M. Onraedt. Bull. Jard. Bot. Belg. 51: 41 - 103." title="Le genre Plagiochila (Dum.) Dum. (Hepaticae) a Madagascar et aux Mascareignes, principalement d'apres les recoltes de M. Onraedt" type="journal article" year="1981">VANDEN BERGHEN, 1981</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
